  "prompt": "What hotel in Darjeeling Hill-station would be safe for unmarried couples, without the harassment of police, hotel staff, and moral police?",
  "response": "In Darjeeling, as in many parts of India, unmarried couples may face challenges due to societal norms and outdated regulations. However, many hotels and guesthouses are now more accommodating and respectful of privacy. Here are some tips and options for a safe and hassle-free stay:\n\n### **Safe and Couple-Friendly Hotels in Darjeeling:**\n1. **The Elgin Darjeeling**  \n   - A heritage hotel known for its professionalism and hospitality.  \n   - Respects guest privacy and is couple-friendly.  \n\n2. **Mayfair Darjeeling**  \n   - A luxury hotel with a reputation for excellent service.  \n   - Discreet and respectful staff who prioritize guest comfort.  \n\n3. **Cedar Inn**  \n   - A boutique hotel that is known for being couple-friendly.  \n   - Offers privacy and comfortable stays.  \n\n4. **Windamere Hotel**  \n   - A colonial-era hotel that is welcoming to all guests, including unmarried couples.  \n   - Ensures a peaceful and respectful environment.  \n\n5. **Hotel Seven Seventeen**  \n   - A mid-range hotel that is popular among couples.  \n   - No unnecessary questioning or interference.  \n\n### **Tips for a Safe Stay:**\n1. **Book in Advance:** Choose reputed hotels or guesthouses that explicitly mention being couple-friendly.  \n2. **Carry Valid IDs:** Both partners should have government-issued identification (Aadhar card, passport, etc.).  \n3. **Opt for Online Booking Platforms:** Use websites like **Booking.com**, **OYO**, or **MakeMyTrip**, which often list couple-friendly hotels.  \n4. **Avoid Budget or Local Guesthouses:** These are more likely to enforce traditional norms.  \n5. **Be Discreet:** Avoid drawing unnecessary attention to your relationship status.  \n\n### **Important Note:**  \nWhile Darjeeling is relatively liberal compared to other parts of India, it\u2019s essential to research and confirm with the hotel beforehand to ensure they are genuinely couple-friendly. Always read recent reviews and check for any red flags regarding harassment or intrusive behavior.  \n\nIf you face any issues, remain calm and assertive, and contact the hotel management or local authorities if necessary. Safe travels!",
